The paper deals with image patch representation and recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of probabilistic framework and machine learning techniques such as collaborative representation and outlier suppression suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of benchmark datasets and performance evaluation indicates that it could also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
